        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "P. Thus we also have that no roots of P' lie on the sides of the convex hull of P, unless they are also roots of P.",
        "bbox": [
          0.5568627450980392,
          0.06606060606060606,
          0.9192156862745098,
          0.09636363636363636
        ],
        "order": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1999_Solutions_1999s_page_003_11",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "From this we conclude that if r is a root of P which is a vertex of the convex hull of the roots, and which is not also a root of P', then f has a single pole at r (as r cannot be a root of P\"). On the other hand, if r is a root of P which is also a root of P', it is a multiple root, and then f has a double pole at r.",
        "bbox": [
          0.5568627450980392,
          0.1,
          0.92,
          0.18787878787878787
        ],
        "order": 3
      }
    ]
  },
