        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "B–1 The answer is 1/3. Let G be the point obtained by re- flecting C about the line AB. Since ∠ADC = π−θ , find that ∠BDE = π − θ − ∠ADC = π−− = ∠ADC = π − ∠BDC = π − ∠BDG, so that E, D, G are collinear. Hence",
        "bbox": [
