        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1999_Solutions_1999s_page_003_17",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "B–4 (based on work by Daniel Stronger) We make repeated use of the following fact: if f is a differentiable function on all of R, limx→−∞f (x) ≥ 0, and f (x) > 0 for all x ∈ R, then f (x) > 0 for all x ∈ R. (Proof: if f (y) < 0 for some x, then f (x) < f (y) for all x < y since f ′ > 0, but then limx→−∞f(x) ≤ f (y) < 0.)",
        "bbox": [
          0.5247058823529411,
          0.5733333333333334,
          0.92,
          0.6624242424242425
        ],
        "order": 13
      }
    ]
