        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Second solution (by Greg Kuperberg): Let f(x) = P′(x) /P(x) = 1/Q(x). By hypothesis, f has at most two poles (counting multiplicity).",
        "bbox": [
          0.12627450980392158,
